&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the Americas benefits plans and associated vendor/broker relationships as well as the annual US Open Enrollment cycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze and enhance the overall benefits and healthcare process workflows and technology solutions, with a focus on optimizing benefits operations with key stakeholders such as Payroll, Human Capital Operations/HRIS, Human Capital Business Partners, Legal, and Employee Relations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the Americas retirement plan/wealth advisory strategy, governance and operations, including 401(k) and RRSP with a focus on enhancing the long-term financial well-being of employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute benefits and wellness strategies by benchmarking market/peer firm practices, identifying gaps, and implementing innovative, market-leading solutions that align with KKR’s culture and values&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enhance the benefits governance framework and drive operational efficiencies across all benefits programs and systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Finance/Payroll teams to ensure thorough analysis, trend forecasting, and budgeting to drive effective business planning for both short- and long-term needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the development and delivery of effective marketing strategies, communication materials and policy documents for Americas benefits and wellness programs&lt;/li&gt;
