&lt;li&gt;Support strategic initiatives aimed at improving service levels, compliance, and cost savings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain alignment between travel policy, company values, and business objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help establish governance practices and performance review cadences for the travel program.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Vendor &amp;amp; Supplier Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate in the selection, negotiation, and management of key travel vendors (e.g., TMCs, airlines, hotels, ground transportation and corporate card).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor vendor SLAs, KPIs, and service delivery, holding partners accountable to performance standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support consolidation efforts, preferred supplier programs, and regional/global alignment of vendor contracts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Efficiency &amp;amp; Cost Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to streamline travel operations, optimize spending, and improve contract terms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze travel program data to recommend changes that reduce costs without compromising service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Finance and Procurement to track savings and budget compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Traveler Experience &amp;amp; Compliance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
