&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2–4 years of experience in invest

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMPANY OVERVIEW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;KKR is a leading global investment firm that offers alternative asset management as well as capital markets and insurance solutions. KKR aims to generate attractive investment returns by following a patient and disciplined investment approach, employing world-class people, and supporting growth in its portfolio companies and communities. KKR sponsors investment funds that invest in private equity, credit and real assets and has strategic partners that manage hedge funds. KKR’s insurance subsidiaries offer retirement, life and reinsurance products under the management of Global Atlantic Financial Group. References to KKR’s investments may include the activities of its sponsored funds and insurance subsidiaries.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Content Specialist to join our marketing team. This role will primarily support KKR&#39;s insurance business, Global Atlantic, while also contributing to content initiatives across the broader firm.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This is an ideal role for a strong financial communicator with exceptional writing and editing skills who enjoys finding creative ways to repurpose, atomize, and adapt content for different audiences, channels, and formats. This candidate will apply AI and emerging technologies to enhance content creation, marketing workflows, and use data to measure and optimize audience engagement. This individual will also help define and scale AI-enabled content practices across the marketing organization, identifying opportunities to improve how content is created, reused and distributed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate enjoys writing a range of content from thought leadership to product marketing and social media posts. In addition to creating content, this individual will work with editorial leads to shape content strategy by determining how information should be positioned, packaged, and distributed to achieve business and marketing objectives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position will be based in our Boston, Hartford, or Des Moines office.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create compelling marketing content and messaging to support KKR&#39;s insurance business, including variable, fixed, and fixed index annuity products, while contributing to broader firmwide content initiatives as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop B2B and B2C content across multiple channels, including web, email, social media, video, presentations, thought leadership, sales enablement materials, and print.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with product marketing, sales, investment professionals, designers, and other stakeholders to develop content that supports strategic marketing and business objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help define and scale AI-enabled content practices by identifying opportunities to incorporate generative AI into content development, editorial workflows, and marketing processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply digital content best practices, including SEO/AEO, email optimization, subject lines, calls to action, and channel-specific content strategies to improve engagement and performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure consistency in messaging, style, tone, and brand voice across all content and marketing initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Write and edit a variety of content formats, including articles, web copy, video scripts, presentations, executive messaging, and thought leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate across Marketing, Legal, Compliance, and business teams to ensure content accuracy, regulatory compliance, and timely delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage multiple projects simultaneously, balancing competing priorities and delivering high-quality work in a fast-paced environment with tight deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMPANY OVERVIEW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;KKR is a leading global investment firm that offers alternative asset management as well as capital markets and insurance solutions. KKR aims to generate attractive investment returns by following a patient and disciplined investment approach, employing world-class people, and supporting growth in its portfolio companies and communities. KKR sponsors investment funds that invest in private equity, credit and real assets and has strategic partners that manage hedge funds. KKR’s insurance subsidiaries offer retirement, life and reinsurance products under the management of Global Atlantic Financial Group. References to KKR’s investments may include the activities of its sponsored funds and insurance subsidiaries.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TEAM OVERVIEW&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The KKR Next Generation Technology (NGT) team invests in traditional growth equity and growth‐oriented majority transactions, with equity checks ranging from $50m to $300m primarily within five main sectors: enterprise software/AI, cybersecurity, infrastructure software, financial technology, and tech-enabled services. NGT’s first fund was over $700M, second fund was $2.2B, and third fund was $3B AUM. The team is now raising Fund IV (targeting $3.5B), and is already actively deploying capital from the fund.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team is looking to add an Associate to the New York office in a career track role. At the outset, the Associate role will likely be a 50/50 split between deal sourcing and execution and over time the execution work and portfolio company management will likely outweigh the sourcing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;QUALIFICATIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The ideal candidate is someone with ~2+ years of investment banking experience plus 1-2 years of growth equity, late-stage venture capital, or private equity experience. Experience in deal sourcing is a plus.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be successful in the role, a candidate should exhibit:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;KKR’s core values, in particular: unquestioned integrity, a strong work ethic, and a commitment to teamwork and excellence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Aptitude for critical and creative thinking across the quantitative and qualitative spectrum&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to learn quickly with clear intellectual curiosity and self-motivation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to multi-task, prioritize and work both independently and within teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Outstanding academic record and demonstrated leadership ability&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interest in deal sourcing strongly preferred; prior sourcing experience is a plus but not required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
